        "body": "~~(based on #2344)~~\r\n\r\nAfter the [recent universal2 wheel work](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1810737) I realized how messy our Python setup is:\r\nA big home-grown solution inside a `setup.py` reinventing half of Python package management all over again.\r\n\r\nThere must be something better for it.\r\nThere is: [maturin](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/).\r\n\r\nTried and trusted [in other projects](https://github.com/mozilla/mozfun-local), this tool can take care of most of the build and development hassles of a Python package with UniFFI bindings.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThis PR switches our development tooling over to maturin, for both local development and on CI.\r\nAnd while I was at it I also moved all Python tooling configuration into the one and only `pyproject.toml`.\r\n\r\nThis is not yet ready for merge, because:\r\n\r\n* [x] Waiting on a release that will include https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/pull/1416\r\n  * CI is probably broken at the moment\r\n* [x] UniFFI 0.23 (upcoming) will move things around, we probably want to have that first, then see how maturin needs to adopt that\r\n* [x] Ensure the release tasks on CI work\r\n  * Might need some test runs pushing to https://test.pypi.org/\r\n* [ ] Remove check requirements on GitHub for `Python 3_6 tests`, `Python 3_6 tests minimum dependencies` and `Python 3_9 tests minimum dependencies` as those tests are gone.",
